name: Int32x4
comment: Interface of Dart Int32x4 and operations. Int32x4 stores 4 32-bit bit-masks in "lanes". The lanes are "x", "y", "z", and "w" respectively.

flagW.name: flagW
flagW.comment: Extracted w value. Returns false for 0, true for any other value.

flagX.name: flagX
flagX.comment: Extracted x value. Returns false for 0, true for any other value.

flagY.name: flagY
flagY.comment: Extracted y value. Returns false for 0, true for any other value.

flagZ.name: flagZ
flagZ.comment: Extracted z value. Returns false for 0, true for any other value.

signMask.name: signMask
signMask.comment: Extract the top bit from each lane return them in the first 4 bits.

fromFloat32x4Bits.name: fromFloat32x4Bits
fromFloat32x4Bits.comment: Returns a bit-wise copy of dart-typed_data.Int32x4.Int32x4-fromFloat32x4Bits.x as a Int32x4.

select.name: select
select.comment: Merge dart-typed_data.Int32x4.select.trueValue and dart-typed_data.Int32x4.select.falseValue based on this' bit mask: Select bit from dart-typed_data.Int32x4.select.trueValue when bit in this is on. Select bit from dart-typed_data.Int32x4.select.falseValue when bit in this is off.

shuffle.name: shuffle
shuffle.comment: Shuffle the lane values. dart-typed_data.Int32x4.shuffle.mask must be one of the 256 shuffle constants.

shuffleMix.name: shuffleMix
shuffleMix.comment: Shuffle the lane values in this and dart-typed_data.Int32x4.shuffleMix.other. The returned Int32x4 will have XY lanes from this and ZW lanes from dart-typed_data.Int32x4.shuffleMix.other. Uses the same dart-typed_data.Int32x4.shuffleMix.mask as dart-typed_data.Int32x4.shuffle.

toString.name: toString
toString.comment: Returns a string representation of this object.

withFlagW.name: withFlagW
withFlagW.comment: Returns a new dart-typed_data.Int32x4 copied from this with a new w value.

withFlagX.name: withFlagX
withFlagX.comment: Returns a new dart-typed_data.Int32x4 copied from this with a new x value.

withFlagY.name: withFlagY
withFlagY.comment: Returns a new dart-typed_data.Int32x4 copied from this with a new y value.

withFlagZ.name: withFlagZ
withFlagZ.comment: Returns a new dart-typed_data.Int32x4 copied from this with a new z value.

withW.name: withW
withW.comment: Returns a new dart-typed_data.Int32x4 copied from this with a new w value.

withX.name: withX
withX.comment: Returns a new dart-typed_data.Int32x4 copied from this with a new x value.

withY.name: withY
withY.comment: Returns a new dart-typed_data.Int32x4 copied from this with a new y value.

withZ.name: withZ
withZ.comment: Returns a new dart-typed_data.Int32x4 copied from this with a new z value.

hashCode.name: hashCode
hashCode.comment:
Get a hash code for this object.

All objects have hash codes. Hash codes are guaranteed to be the same for objects that are equal when compared using the equality operator ==. Other than that there are no guarantees about the hash codes. They will not be consistent between runs and there are no distribution guarantees.

If a subclass overrides dart-typed_data.Int32x4.hashCode it should override the equality operator as well to maintain consistency.

runtimeType.name: runtimeType
runtimeType.comment: A representation of the runtime type of the object.

==.comment:
The equality operator.

The default behavior for all dart-core.Objects is to return true if and only if this and dart-typed_data.Int32x4.==.other are the same object.

Override this method to specify a different equality relation on a class. The overriding method must still be an equivalence relation. That is, it must be:

  • Total: It must return a boolean for all arguments. It should never throw or return null.

  • Reflexive: For all objects o, o == o must be true.

  • Symmetric: For all objects o1 and o2, o1 == o2 and o2 == o1 must either both be true, or both be false.

  • Transitive: For all objects o1, o2, and o3, if o1 == o2 and o2 == o3 are true, then o1 == o3 must be true.

The method should also be consistent over time, so equality of two objects should not change over time, or at least only change if one of the objects was modified.

If a subclass overrides the equality operator it should override the dart-typed_data.Int32x4.hashCode method as well to maintain consistency.

noSuchMethod.name: noSuchMethod
noSuchMethod.comment:
dart-typed_data.Int32x4.noSuchMethod is invoked when users invoke a non-existent method on an object. The name of the method and the arguments of the invocation are passed to dart-typed_data.Int32x4.noSuchMethod in an dart-core.Invocation. If dart-typed_data.Int32x4.noSuchMethod returns a value, that value becomes the result of the original invocation.

The default behavior of dart-typed_data.Int32x4.noSuchMethod is to throw a dart-core.NoSuchMethodError.

toString.name: toString
toString.comment: Returns a string representation of this object.
